quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  7,105,"I am obliged to say nothing concerning Allah except the truth. I have come to you with clear proof from your Lord, so let the Children of Israel go with me.”"
  7,106,"Pharaoh said, “If you have brought a sign, then bring it forth if you are truthful.”"
  7,107,"So he threw his staff, and it suddenly became a real serpent."
  7,108,"And he drew out his hand, and it was shining white to the beholders."
  7,109,"The chiefs among Pharaoh’s people said, “This is indeed a learned magician!"
  7,110,"He seeks to drive you out of your land. [Pharaoh said], “So what do you advise?”"
  7,111,"They said, “Let him and his brother wait for a while and send heralds to the cities"
  7,112,"to bring you every learned magician.”"
  7,113,"The magicians came to Pharaoh and said, “Will we have a reward if we prevail?”"
  7,114,"He said, “Yes, and you will surely be of those who are close to me.”"
  7,115,"They said, “O Moses, will you throw first or will we be the first to throw?”"
  7,116,"He said, “You throw first.” So when they threw, they enchanted the eyes of the people and struck terror into them, and produced a powerful magic."
  7,117,"We inspired Moses, “Throw your staff,” and it suddenly swallowed up all their illusionary devices."
  7,118,"Thus the truth prevailed, and all what they did was proven to be false."
  7,119,"They were defeated right there and were utterly humiliated."
  7,120,"The magicians fell down in prostration,"